<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN368-intro">tiṇai, vākai tuṟai, maṟakkaḷavaḻi. cēramāṉ kuṭakkōneṭuñcēralātaṉ cōḻaṉvēṟpaḵṟaṭakkaipperunaṟkiḷḷiyoṭu pōrppuṟattup porutuvīḻantāraṅkaḻattaṉṉatāka uyirpōkātu kiṭantāṉaik kaḻāttalaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN368">
<l>kaḷiṟu mukantu peyarkuva meṉiṉē</l>
<l>yoḷiṟumaḻai tavirkkuṅ  kuṉṟam pōlak</l>
<l>kaimmā vellāṅ kaṇaiyiṭat tolaintaṉa</l>
<l>koṭuñci neṭuntēr mukakkuva meṉiṉē</l>
<l>kaṭumpari naṉmāṉ vāṅkuvayi ṉolki</l>
<l>neṭumpī ṭaḻintu nilañcērn taṉavē</l>
<l>koycuvaṟ puravi mukakkuva meṉiṉē</l>
<l>meyniṟainta vaḻuvoṭu perumpiṟi tāki</l>
<l>vaḷivaḻak kaṟutta vaṅkam pōlak</l>
<l>kuruti yamperum puṉalkūrntaṉavē</l>
<l>yāṅka, mukavai yiṉmaiyi ṉukavai yiṉṟi</l>
<l>yirappō riraṅku <supplied>mi</supplied>ṉṉā viyaṉkaḷat</l>
<l>tāḷaḻip paṭutta vāḷē ruḻava</l>
<l>kaṭāa yāṉai kālvaḻi yaṉṉavaṉ</l>
<l>ṟeṭārit teṇkaṇ ṭeḷirppa voṟṟip</l>
<l>pāṭi vanta tellāṅ kōṭiyar</l>
<l>muḻavumaru ṟirumaṇi miṭaintaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉaravuṟa ḻāra mukakkuva meṉavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">If we were to come back after bringing in elephant bulls, </l>
<l corresp="2">like hills that retain bright clouds </l>
<l corresp="3">all [those] hand animals would be lost when arrows were put [into them]. </l>
<l corresp="4">If we were to draw in tall chariots with support staffs, </l>
<l corresp="5">the fast-moving fine horses becoming weary on the curved side, </l>
<l corresp="6">[their] long pride perishing they would join the ground. </l>
<l corresp="7">If we were to draw in horses with trimmed manes, </l>
<l corresp="8">with scars that fill [their] bodies, encountering the great other, </l>
<l corresp="9">like ships when the movement of the wind is cut off, </l>
<l corresp="10">they would fill a great flood of blood. Thus, </l>
<l corresp="11">In the absence of things to bring in, without things that drop, </l>
<l corresp="12">on the unpleasant wide field where those who beg are aggrieved, </l>
<l corresp="13">o you ploughman who ploughs with a sword that destroys men, </l>
<l corresp="15">loudly beating the clear eye of my Teṭāri drum </l>
<l corresp="14">that is like the way of a rutting elephant’s foot </l>
<l corresp="16">singing came all the dancers, </l>
<l corresp="18">thinking “we will draw from you snake-like [gem-]strings </l>
<l corresp="17">that are close-set with brilliant gems [large] as drums. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
